main event: A tear-shaped object, the size of a football, was observed falling from west to east for 5 seconds with a bright tail and no sound.
interesting points: The object was described as a bluish flash.
The report indicates the object was likely an ordinary meteor.
The object was observed at 2401Z (local time 2253) on April 24, 1963 in Cloquet, Minnesota.
The sighting was made by the Chief of Guards at the Wood Conversion Company in Cloquet.
Weather conditions were clear with winds from 270 degrees at 5 knots.
sighted object: tear-shaped object, size of a football
witnesses: Chief of Guards, Wood Conversion Company
